@node "Document_0" "Introduction"
@next "Document_2"
@prev "Main"
@{b}What is BämsBackdropBrowser?@{ub}

If you have ever created a homepage, or wanted to
change your WBbackdrop, you know that it's really
hard to say if a picture will look good or not,
when you just see one copy of it.
This is easily solved by BämsBackdropBrowser!
Just load it in and it will cover an entire screen
with your picture, and you'll see right away if
it's good enough.

BämsBackdropBrowser has been tested, and works
perfectly on:
A4000/030/18MB RAM/340MB HD
A1200/020/2 MB RAM/85MB HD

Picture loading is accomplished via datatypes (not
included).
@endnode

@node "Document_2" "System Requirements"
@next "Document_3"
@prev "Document_1"
@{b}What do I need to run BämsBackdropBrowser?@{ub}

You'll need an Amiga with at least AmigaOS 3.0.
@endnode

@node "Document_3" "Usage"
@next "Document_4"
@prev "Document_2"
@{b}How do I use BämsBackdropBrowser?@{ub}

@{i}From WorkBench:@{ui}

Doubleclick the BBdB
icon. An ASL filerequester will appear. Choose
the file(s) you wish to view.

@{i}From CLI:@{ui}

BBdB NAME, ALL/S
NAME: The name of the picture, supports wildcards (#?).
      If you type in the name of a directory, a file-
      requester will appear.
ALL:  View all images in all subdirs?

@{i}In program:@{ui}

<ESC> Quit
<RETURN> or <SPACE> View next pic.
<1> to <9> Remember pic. This works only if
you have chosen many pics. When you have viewed
all pics, the Remembered pics will be shown
again.
<c> Copy filename to clipboard.
<C> Copy filename with full path to clipboard.
@endnode

